 It's been more than a year since a fire gutted parts of Parliament and at least one union has accused presiding officers of dragging their feet over repairs. For more, eNCA speaks to Parliamentary Speaker Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - National Assembly speaker Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula says Nehawu's concerns over the lack of progress over repairs to Parliament are unfortunate and misplaced. The National Health and Allied Workers Union has expressed concerns about the slow progress in finalising a report into the fire. READ: Parliament fire | DA says alternative venue a priority It says this has delayed the process of holding those responsible to account. Mapisa-Nqakula says the union has many avenues to address their concerns.